
@startuml

' Define classes
class ResearchGroup {
    +id: int
    +name: String
}

class Department {
    +id: int
    +name: String
}

class Researcher {
    +id: int
    +name: String
    -researchGroup: ResearchGroup (1)
}

class Project {
    +id: int
    +title: String
}

class WorkPackage {
    +id: int
    +description: String
    +startDate: Date
    +endDate: Date
    -leader: ResearchGroup (1)
}

class TeamAssignment {
    +id: int
    +startDate: Date
    +endDate: Date (optional)
    -researcher: Researcher (1)
    -workPackage: WorkPackage (1)
}

' Relationships
Department "1" -- "*" ResearchGroup : contains
ResearchGroup "1" -- "*" Researcher : has members
Project "1" -- "*" WorkPackage : decomposed into
WorkPackage "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : led by {composition}
WorkPackage "1" -- "*" TeamAssignment : has team assignments
TeamAssignment "1" -- "1" Researcher : assigned researcher
TeamAssignment "1" -- "1" WorkPackage : assigned to WP

' Notes for traceability of service delivery
note right of TeamAssignment
  Service delivery must be traceable.
  When a researcher changes groups,
  old assignments are terminated and new ones created.
end note

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Key Elements:

- **ResearchGroup**:
  - Each group belongs to a **Department**.
  - A **Researcher** belongs to exactly one **ResearchGroup**.

- **WorkPackage**:
  - A **Project** is decomposed into multiple **WorkPackages**.
  - Each **WorkPackage** is led by one **ResearchGroup**.

- **TeamAssignment**:
  - Represents a **Researcher** being assigned to a **WorkPackage**.
  - Tracks start and end dates for accurate service delivery recording.
  - If a researcher changes groups or a WP leader changes, assignments are updated accordingly.

